For &lt;a rel="noreferrer nofollow"&gt;Monthly Scavenger Hunt&lt;/a&gt; - &lt;b&gt;Ovoid&lt;/b&gt;
It may not be a &lt;i&gt;regular&lt;/i&gt; ovoid, but it is at least vaguely egg shaped in cross-section   (A sort of &lt;i&gt;hand drawn&lt;/i&gt; ovoid, maybe...)
Sutton Park

A new scheme being trialled (launches properly on 8 March)- there are bikes in the Town Centre and outside the Leisure Centre at Wyndley Gate
&lt;a href="https://www.bikebiz.com/west-midlands-cycle-hire-scheme-launches-in-sutton-coldfield/" rel="noreferrer nofollow"&gt;More here&lt;/a&gt; 
&lt;a href="https://www.wmcyclehire.co.uk/" rel="noreferrer nofollow"&gt;Offical Website &lt;/a&gt;

The Jamboree Stone commemorates the 1957 World Jamboree held in the Park. A second plaque was added to commemorate the centenary of the Scout movement in 2007

&amp;quot;This paque commemorates the World Jubilee Jamboree of the Scout movement which was held in this park from August 1st to 12th 1957 and was opeend by H.R.H. The Duke of Gloucester.  32,000 Scouts from 87 parts of the world came here and were visited by Her Majesty Queen Ekizabeth II and H.T.H. Prince Philip Duke of Edinburgh and many other Distingusihed persons.&amp;quot;
Sutton Park
